+# Nym Testing Environment
+This is a fork of the original [Nym Project](https://github.com/nymtech/nym) intended for testing vulnerabilities against a custom Nym network. We are using the [Shadow Network Simulator](https://shadow.github.io/) to simulate our network. We assume that you have installed Shadow and added it to your path.
+To install Nym, clone this and follow the steps in the original README below to build.
+To run the simulation, run the following commands:
+```
+cd shadow
+```
+Initialize the node configuration. This only needs to be run once.
+```
+sh init.sh 
+```
+Run the Shadow simulation.
+```
+sh runshadow.sh
+```
+This may take a few minutes.
+## Fragment Delays
+For this attack to work, the victim's gateway must drop the victim's *outgoing* packets at random. This way, the victim will
+retransmit fragments that did not receive an ACK after a certain timeframe. This will cause delays on the recipient's end.
+In order to determine which fragment set was sent by the victim, we must set a threshold for the delay. If the fragment
+set's delay is higher than the threshold, it was sent by the victim. This way, we can account for unexpected delays of other,
+unrelated packets that could cause false detections.
+The fragment set delay is defined as the time between the arrival of the first and the last fragment of a set.
+In our simulation, Alice is the victim and Bob is the attacker.
+
+After running the simulation, run the following command to interpret the results:
+```
+python timestamps.py 3
+```
+The output shows the delays of each fragment set the attacker received, including ones from normal clients not belonging
+to the victim. The detection of the victim's fragment set depends on the threshold, which is passed as an argument at the end.
+You may change the threshold to your liking. For our purposes, a threshold of 3 seconds seems to be optimal.
+
+If you wish to run multiple tests at once, run the following command:
+```
+sh runtests.sh
+```
+The tests may take several minutes to complete. The results will be written to  ```shadow/tests/testlog```.
+Please note that this will reset previously generated client keys.
+
+## Navigating Shadow
+In order to read the output of the simulation, you may run
+```cd shadow.data/hosts/``` and then ```ls```. This will list all the actors (*hosts*) in our simulation. The ```validator.nymtech.net```
+host is a dummy for the Nym-API and serves no other purpose.
+Each host has its own directory containing the standard and error output, which you can view with the text editor of your choice,
+or by using the ```cat``` command.
+
+## Troubleshooting
+If issues arise, it's worth trying the following:
+- Clearing the client_keys directory and running ```sh init.sh``` again
+- Clearing the ```~/.nym``` directory in your home directory and running ```sh init.sh```(**WARNING:** this also contains Nym data unrelated to this project)
+- Increasing the simulation duration in the ```shadow/shadow.yaml``` configuration file and running the simulation again
+
+If none of these work, or you simply wish to take a look under the hood, you can look through the outputs of the simulation
+as described above.
+
+Below is the original README of the Nym project.
+
